description:

• Dimension: 38 x 38mm round

name: Wearable Planter No. 3 Geometric Necklace, by Wearable Planter
description:
Why should your plants stay at home? They help clean the air you breathe, are beautiful, and create a wonderful conversation starter. Carry a sprout, a succulent, or a flower you found on your morning walk. This necklace lets you bring smiles along with greenery where ever you go!

I created the design for the Wearable Planter using modeling software. It is then 3D printed and finished by hand. 

This planter is an experiment with new materials. It is made out of a translucent 3D printed acrylic polymer. The vessel itself is a slightly yellow translucent, allowing you to see the roots or the bottom of a plant. This material is watertight, and acts as a perfect vase to carry a bud or a sprout on your days adventures.

Comes with directions on how to add plants and recommendations on which work best. Sorry, but no plants are included with this item.

Photo#4-5 is color sample, #4 is Red and #5 is Blue

Product photos & description: Wearable Planter

Why should your plants stay at home? They help clean the air you breathe, are beautiful, and create a wonderful conversation starter. Carry a sprout, a succulent, or a flower you found on your morning walk.

I created the design for the Wearable Planter using modeling software. It is then 3D printed and finished by hand. This item is made out of black 3D printed acrylic and is hand polished for a smooth finish. The result of hand finishing these pieces is they have a luster that resembles that of the finest wooden clarinets.

Comes with directions on how to add plants and recommendations on which work best. Sorry, but no plants are included with this item.

Photo#3-5 is color sample, #3-4 is translucent and #5 is orange

Product photos & description: Wearable Planter

name: Icosahedron Wearable Planter Necklace, by Wearable Planter
description:
Bring a plant with you on your day's adventure! Plants help clean the air you breathe, are beautiful, and create a wonderful conversation starter (it's also believed that exposure to plants throughout the day can make you more intelligent- but I make no claims to this). Carry a sprout, a succulent, or a flower you found on your morning walk.

Ultramarine is a color with a very rich history. During the renaissance, the dyes that produced this color cost more than gold.

The form for this wearable planter is inspired by the icosahedron- a 20 plane surface and one of the platonic solids. I created the design for the Wearable Planter using modeling software. It is then 3D printed, polished, and dyed by hand. 

Comes with directions on how to add plants and recommendations on which work best. Sorry, but no plants are included with this item.

Photo #4 is Teal, photo #5 is Coral

Product photos & description: Wearable Planter

name: Miniature Icosahedron, by Wearable Planter
description:
Wouldn't you like to carry around a small plant with you during the day? This necklace will let you do just that, and also bring conversation, joy, and fresh air along with you. The icosahedron is a form that has inspired artists and scientists for centuries with its symmetry and elegance. This piece adds a pop of color and a bit of geometric flair to any outfit as well!

The original idea for the wearable planter came from the desire to create something with an heirloom quality out of plastic. It's a material that last for thousands of years, yet its applications are usually only temporary. This solves that inherent contradiction in use, something beautiful can be made out of this material. 

This wearable planter is created digitally with modeling software and is then 3d printed out of nylon and hand dyed a lovely tangerine and sealed. This planter works best with a clipping from a succulent that has been allowed to take root.

This planter measures 6/10" in diameter and comes on a 29" long leather cord. 

Products Photos & description: Wearable Planter

name: Twisted Handlebar Vase, by Wearable Planter
description:
Ever dreamed of carrying some flowers on your bike? Why not carry them on your handlebar for the whole world to see? If you've been wanting to make your green form of transportation greener, you can carry a small bunch of flowers in this twisted vase for your handlebars. This bike planter is created digitally with modeling software and is then 3d printed out of nylon and dyed to a bold royal blue. It clips onto your handlebars and stays in place with tension.

Don't know which size to order? The small clip will fit on the handlebars of most bikes with 7/8" diameter and above. The large clip is 1" in diameter, and will fit on bikes with handlebars thicker than that diameter and over grips and grip tape.

Sorry, but this item does not come with flowers.

Products photos & description: wearbleplanter

name: Bike Planter, by Wearable Planter
description:
Do you love riding bikes? What about plants? Bring your plants on an adventure and let them enjoy some sunshine and fresh air! If you’ve ever dreamed about attaching a plant to your bike, now you’re in luck! This bike planter is made with 3D printing tehcnology, so not only will you be showing off your love of nature, but you’ll be showing off a little piece of the future.

This planter attaches firmly to your bike with an elastic nylon cord, and will fit snugly on most tube sizes. And you’ll have to supply your own plant and bicycle to make your next adventure fully amazing!

This bike planter is created digitally with modeling software and is then 3d printed out of nylon and hand dyed orange and sealed. Due to the hand dying process, the color of this planter may vary slightly. This planter works best with a clipping from a succulent that has been allowed to take root or a large air plant.

Measures 2.3” tall, 1.4” wide, and 1” deep. 

Product photos & Description: wearableplanter

It has leather back pocket for your credit cards, tickets or money. They will be secured in the pocket nicely and you can go out without carrying too many things!
